title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Create a plan that loads waiting list data for the month “2025-05”, and only have waiting list type that contains the word “Aktiv”, for these compute an contain the waiting list total for each organisation where the total is larger than 10000. For these organisations, the plan must get the total number of moveouts from 2025 and return the organisation name, the total in aktiv waiting list in 2025-05 and total of move outs in 2025. Output should be in textfile.

title: Agent: SpecifierAgent Output
log:
Load the waiting list dataset and the moveouts dataset.

1. From the waiting list dataset, filter records to month = "2025-05".
2. Further filter waiting list records to those whose waiting list type contains the substring "Aktiv" (case-sensitive matching as provided).
3. Group the filtered waiting list records by organisation and compute the waiting list total per organisation for 2025-05.
4. Keep only organisations whose waiting list total (from step 3) is greater than 10000.

5. From the moveouts dataset, filter records to year = 2025.
6. Group the 2025 moveouts records by organisation and compute the total number of moveouts per organisation for 2025.

7. Join the organisations retained in step 4 with the moveouts totals from step 6 on organisation.
8. For each joined organisation, produce a record with:
   - organisation name
   - waiting list total for "Aktiv" in 2025-05
   - total number of moveouts in 2025

9. Output the resulting records to a text file.

log.thoughts: Task requires waiting-list rows for year_month = '2025-05' filtered by waiting_list_type containing 'Aktiv' and aggregating totals per organisation (factwaitinglists.total). To return organisation names we need the organisation table (organisation.organisation_id -> organisation.name). To get move-out totals for 2025 we need factmoveouts (move_out_year = 2025, sum_of_move_outs). These three tables are necessary and sufficient to compute the requested output. No input text files are required; output will be written to a text file by the plan executor.

steps.detailed_description: Load the three input tables: factwaitinglists (all columns), factmoveouts (all columns), and organisation (all columns). These are JDBC inputs and will be the sources for subsequent filtering, aggregation, and join steps.

Perform the following parallel unary transformations on the inputs loaded in step 1:
- On factwaitinglists: 1) Filter rows where month = 5 and year_month = '2025-05' (ensure month numeric equals 5 and year_month equals '2025-05'). 2) Filter the remaining rows to keep only those where waiting_list_type contains the substring 'Aktiv' (case-sensitive match). 3) Group by organisation_id and compute waiting_list_total = SUM(total) for each organisation (this yields one aggregated dataset of waiting_list_total per organisation for 2025-05). 4) Filter the grouped results to keep only organisations where waiting_list_total > 10000.
- On factmoveouts: 1) Filter rows where move_out_year = 2025. 2) Group by organisation_id and compute moveouts_total = SUM(sum_of_move_outs) for each organisation (this yields one aggregated dataset of 2025 moveouts per organisation).
Output: two aggregated datasets: (A) filtered_waitinglist_totals[organisation_id, waiting_list_total] and (B) moveouts_2025_totals[organisation_id, moveouts_total].

Join the aggregated datasets and enrich with organisation name: 1) Inner-join the filtered_waitinglist_totals (from step 2) with moveouts_2025_totals (from step 2) on organisation_id to retain only organisations present in both (this produces [organisation_id, waiting_list_total, moveouts_total]). 2) Join the result with organisation (loaded in step 1) on organisation.organisation_id = joined.organisation_id to attach organisation.name. Output: dataset containing [organisation_id, name, waiting_list_total, moveouts_total].

Write the resulting records from step 3 to a text file. Each output record should contain: organisation name, waiting_list_total for 'Aktiv' in 2025-05, and moveouts_total for 2025. Use a line-based text output (one organisation per line) in the requested textfile destination.

log.thoughts: I loaded all three tables first, then performed both waiting-list and moveout filters/aggregations in a single unary step to keep the plan compact, joined the aggregated results and enriched with organisation.name, and finally wrote the output to a text file.

log.thoughts: Load the three JDBC tables as separate input operators (ids 1..3). Outputs left empty so downstream builders can attach next operators.

operations.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val m = r.getField(4); val ym = r.getField(2); (m != null && m.asInstanceOf[Int] == 5) && (ym != null && ym.toString == "2025-05") }
(r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val t = r.getField(6); t != null && t.toString.contains("Aktiv") }

(r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val orgId = if (r.getField(1) == null) 0 else r.getField(1).asInstanceOf[Int]; val tot = if (r.getField(7) == null) 0 else r.getField(7).asInstanceOf[Int]; (orgId, tot) }
(r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val y = r.getField(4); y != null && y.asInstanceOf[Int] == 2025 }

(r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val orgId = if (r.getField(1) == null) 0 else r.getField(1).asInstanceOf[Int]; val outs = if (r.getField(6) == null) 0 else r.getField(6).asInstanceOf[Int]; (orgId, outs) }
(t: ((Int, Int), (Int, Int))) => { val orgId = t._1._1; val waiting = t._1._2; val moveouts = t._2._2; (orgId, waiting, moveouts) }

(r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val orgId = if (r.getField(0) == null) 0 else r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val name = if (r.getField(3) == null) "" else r.getField(3).toString; (orgId, name) }

(t: ((Int, Int, Int), (Int, String))) => { val left = t._1; val right = t._2; val orgId = left._1; val waiting = left._2; val moveouts = left._3; val name = right._2; (orgId, name, waiting, moveouts) }

log.thoughts: Loaded three JDBC tables, performed the specified filters, maps and aggregations for waiting lists and moveouts, then joined the aggregated results and enriched with organisation name.

operations.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val month = r.getField(4).asInstanceOf[Int]; val ym = r.getField(2).toString; month == 5 && ym == "2025-05" }

(t: ((Int, Int, Int), org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record)) => { val joined = t._1; val orgRec = t._2; val name = orgRec.getField(3).toString; val waiting = joined._2; val moveouts = joined._3; s"${name} | ${waiting} | ${moveouts}" }

log.thoughts: Loaded three JDBC tables, performed the requested filters and aggregations to produce two aggregated datasets, joined them and enriched with organisation name, then formatted for text output.
